sentence: Today's session closes with the NASDAQ Composite Index volume reaching the 10th place in the top ten list for this year.
The last time the index closed above 2.63 billion shares was on Jun 08 2017.
The total shares traded for the NASDAQ was over 3.42 billion.
Advancers stocks led declining by 1.85 to 1 ratio.
There were 1898 advancers and 1025 decliners for the day.
On the NASDAQ Stock Exchange 80 stocks reached a 52 week high and 17 those reaching lows totaled.
The most active, advancers, decliners, unusual volume and most active by dollar volume can be monitored intraday on the Most Active Stocks page.
The NASDAQ 100 index closed up .4% for the day; a total of 23.24 points.
NVIDIA Corporation ( NVDA ) had the largest percent change down (-2.87%) while Liberty Global plc ( LBTYK ) had the largest percent change gain rising 3.96%.
The Dow Jones index closed down -.01% for the day; a total of -2.53 points.
Home Depot, Inc. (The) ( HD ) had the largest percent change down (-2.68%) while Visa Inc. ( V ) had the largest percent change gain rising 1.73%.
